cleanDesc: LTW-Inspired ABS Front Lip - Matte Black - E36 BMW w/ M3 Front Bumpe...
short-description: When looking for a front lip for your BMW, there are a few important factors to consider. Cost, material construction, intended use, and reliability are just a few things to think about. Some people desire lips with hand-laid carbon fiber no matter the cost, others just want whatever is cheapest and fits. Unfortunately, the market has become flooded with numerous examples of both extremes, with few options offering true "best of both worlds" quality. This is where our Turner Motorsport LTW Inspired ABS Front Lip comes in! At the start of this project, we wanted a lip that looks great and offers real downforce benefits, but also doesn't empty our wallets. Designed in-house using 3D scan modeling and CAD, our front lip is a cost-effective, yet highly appealing option with a lot to offer! Made specifically for the M3 front bumper, this ABS front lip is durable, lightweight, and easy to install. This LTW Inspired Front Lip is a perfect alternative to expensive carbon fiber front lips that are prone to failure, and a more rugged option than typical cheaper plastic lips which provide few benefits and offer questionable fitment at best. Utilizing UV stabilized ABS in a two-piece bonded design, this lip has shown to provide the best possible combination of cost-to-performance and retains the clean matte finish of the original E36 trim. If matte black isn't your thing, this lip can easily be prepped and painted to whatever color you desire. Features & Specifications: LTW inspired design Vacuum formed ABS plastic with UV resistant construction 2-Piece bonded design for increased rigidity Designed by TMS engineers using 3D laser scanning & CAD for precision fitment Uses factory self-tapping screws for installation (Need new hardware? See T#599749) Includes pre-applied 3M double-sided adhesive for additional retention and a tight seal against the front bumper

cleanDesc: Turner High Kick Trunk Spoiler - E90 - Gloss Black
short-description: Designed from our original Carbon Fiber High Kick Spoiler, we have developed an ABS High Kick Trunk Spoiler that transforms the look of your E90, all while keeping budget constraints in mind. Constructed from impact and UV resistant ABS plastic, this light and durable spoiler provides a sporty style that's sure to set your vehicle apart from the rest, without the high price of an equivalent carbon fiber spoiler. Installs with no drilling, cutting, or any permanent modifications! Included are two pre-mounted double side adhesive strips for easy installation onto your trunk lid. Simply clean the surface area of the trunk, remove the backing from the already attached high strength double-sided tape, line it up, and press firmly down. We recommend doing this in a warm environment as it will better adhere to the trunk. Features & Specifications: Designed and engineered by Turner Motorsport in-house using state of the art 3D laser scanning and CAD technology for precision fitment. Mimics the design of our carbon fiber version as closely as possible for similar styling. Accentuates the OE body lines throughout the outer edge of the spoiler Utilizes 3M double-sided tape for a strong bond to the body Made from lightweight, vacuum-formed gloss black ABS polymer that is enhanced with UV-stabilizer

cleanDesc: Turner LTW-Inspired Modular ABS Splitter - E36 BMW w/ M3 Front Bumpe...
short-description: Turner Motorsport is proud to offer its brand new E36 LTW-inspired ABS splitter. Designed for use with the M3 front bumper and aftermarket replicas, this ABS splitter is a durable, lightweight alternative to expensive carbon fiber that is prone to cracking or shattering when damaged. Using UV stabilized ABS in a two-piece bonded design has shown to provide the best possible combination of cost-to-performance and retains the clean matte finish of the original E36 trim. Front splitters are an important aerodynamic upgrade that not only changes the look of your car, but also helps to create downforce, improving your vehicles overall handling at higher speeds. Unfortunately, due to their low-slung positioning, they are often susceptible to damage from road debris, uneven roads and driveways, speed bumps, and more. This can often make it hard to justify spending copious amounts on money on a part who's days are numbered, especially when being installed on a vehicle that sees both track and daily driver use.

short-description: This is the Genuine BMW carbon fiber rear spoiler lip which is available as an option on the E92 M3 Competition Package (ZCP). It also fits all 2007 and newer E92 coupes including 328i and 335i. This will replace the original E92 M3 rear lip spoiler. Being an Original BMW part, this lip spoiler fits perfectly and looks amazing. It's made of real carbon fiber (not just a thin layer of carbon over fiberglass, like the cheap alternatives) but also looks great painted in body color. The spoiler matches the curve of the E92 trunklid which gives it a very purposeful and deliberate appearance. Its shape and dimensions have been optimized to reduce aerodynamic lift without being a gung-ho add-on piece. Due to the differences in trunklid shapes, this will not fit E93 convertibles. For the best and longest-lasting installation we recommend using the factory BMW spoiler adhesive (Betalink) and install by an experienced professional.     2007+    BMW 328i, 328xi, 335i, 335xi coupe  2008+    coupe

cleanDesc: Turner Motorsport Carbon Fiber Side Skirts - F82 M4
short-description: Looking to boost the visual appeal of your F82 M4? We are proud to finally offer our very own Turner Motorsport Carbon Fiber Side Skirts! The Carbon Fiber Side Skirts were designed in-house using state of the art 3D laser scanning and CAD modeling for exact precision and fitment. To ensure the side skirts look great and last for years to come, they are constructed using hand laid pre-impregnated 2x2 carbon fiber and then autoclave cured. This ensures the carbon fibers pattern remains perfect and we get even epoxy distribution for greater strength. To finish the side skirts, we apply clear coat for greater longevity and UV protection.    To add an even greater performance aesthetic to both the side skirts and your BMW, we have incorporated winglets, a feature not often included on other side skirt sets. Even better yet, you can choose from two sizes, small or large! These are constructed in the same method as the side skirts and mount at the rear of the side skirts just before the rear tires, giving the side skirt a great racing style. These side skirts mount to the existing rocker cover mounting locations with the included hardware. Features and Specifications: 2x2 twill weave pre-preg carbon fiber, clear coated for UV resistance Can be left as clear coated carbon fiber or painted to color match Optional small or large winglets Hollow underside Reduced width in areas where you might step Mounts to existing rocker cover mounting locations with supplied hardware

As with any carbon fiber or fiberglass body panel, extra time and preparation will be required to ensure the best fitment and installation. While no aftermarket body panels fit as perfectly as original OEM BMW panels, we were very satisfied with the overall quality and fit of these trunk lids. If you are mounting it unpainted to keep the carbon fiber visble, this trunk lid already comes with a clear gelcoat finish so that it is already exactly how you'd want it. cleanDesc: RKP GT Carbon Fiber Roof Panel - 2x2 Weave - E46 Coupe
short-description: When the E46 M3 CSL was released, one of the central talking points of the vehicle was the cutting edge weight saving technologies that were utilized in its construction. The CSL was most notably distinguished from the standard E46 M3 by its various lightweight components. The largest of these is the carbon fiber-reinforced plastic (GFP) roof panel, which weighs over 13 pounds less than its conventional steel counterpart. Many enthusiasts sought after the BMW OEM roof to add to their vehicles, but the part was and is to this day only available to those with a CSL vin #. As an answer to the E46 M3 clients, RKP is proud to introduce the RKP E46 M3 carbon fiber roof panel. Their carbon roofs are constructed by hand at a local facility specializing in components for Grand Am, Time Attack, and various hill climb and formula car classes. Each roof has great fit and finish and saves a considerable amount of weight over the standard roof panel.

short-description: BMW E36 sunroof delete kit will allow you remove 32 lbs from the highest point of the car, which will improve weight distribution and cornering abilities. The fit and finish is base the original OEM specs. The sunroof delete kit is designed to fit original mounting holes with ability to reuse original mounting hardware if needed. For those of you who have removed the sunroof mechanism and left the original metal lid in place you can still save around 10 lbs by installing this kit.

cleanDesc: Seibon CSL style carbon fiber trunk - E92 3 series
short-description: Founded in 2003 Seibon Carbon excels in delivering premium quality carbon fiber products to those with discerning tastes. The process begins with the best carbon raw material manufactured in either USA or France; in fact it is the same stock that can be found on high performance racecars, battleships and satellites. Supporting race teams is one of Seibons' specialties and you will see their work in many different platforms and racing types. Drivers such as Michele Abbate in her Scion FRS racecar, Fredric Aasbo in his Formula D Scion tC and even team RS-R in Asian Formula D all rely solely on Seibon to get them to the podium. Using single piece construction, the carbon is laid inside of a mold instead of being wrapped around it. This allows for a much stronger piece in the end and allows much greater control when the resin is applied. Areas such as door hinges, hood latches and window regulator mounting points are reinforced so as to add strength and longevity through repeated use. Application of the resin is then accomplished using proprietary techniques that allow for a much more uniform coating than most competitors and yields a product that is lighter, since there is no excess. Finally the product is finished with a glossy clear coat this resists chipping and cracking and gives a glossy wet look. Inspection of the finished product is then performed to ensure there is no weave distortion in tight corners or complex bends.

cleanDesc: BMW E36 Coupe Base Kit - E36
short-description: Despite what you've been told, offset is in fact everything. The wider the stance (or track width) the better the grip. In order to achieve a wider stance, the offset must be increased. The only way to make a wide offset look pleasing is with the use of wider fenders or some type of fender flare. Until now, this provided a look that was unpleasant or too "racecar" for some folks. Enter the StreetFighter LA widebody kit. This kit comes with everything you will need to fit the widest wheel/tire combo possible and make it look good at the same time. Made from the highest quality materials, this kit comes ready for paint or the vinyl wrap of your choice. When fully installed it will give the car a dramatically wider stance and a more muscular appearance. Kit Includes: Front Bumper Extensions (2) Front Flares (2) Rear Flares (2) Rear Bumper Extension (2)

cleanDesc: Carbon Fiber Trunk Lid - E46 Convertible
short-description: This CSL inspired trunk lid for 1999-2006 E46 3 series Convertibles and saves precious weight over the heavy steel stock BMW trunk lid. It also looks great, especially if you are into the naked carbon fiber look. This particular trunk lid's styling has a slightly swept up rear edge, reminiscent of the E46 M3 CSL -- which also had a carbon fiber trunk lid with an integral "spoiler" edge built into it.    We were pleasantly surprised by the fit and finish of this trunk lid, particularly at this price. The trunk lid fits as good as any other carbon fiber lid we've come across. Some modifications and provisions need to be made to fit all trunk auxiliary components, such as lighting, trunk latch, hood shocks, emblems and interior trunk trim -- which is why we highly recommend professional installation on these (even if you're not having it painted). As with any carbon fiber or fiberglass body panel, extra time and preparation will be required to ensure the best fitment and installation. While no aftermarket body panels fit as perfectly as original OEM BMW panels, we were very satisfied with the overall quality and fit of these trunk lids. If you are mounting it unpainted to keep the carbon fiber visble, this trunk lid already comes with a clear gelcoat finish so that it is already exactly how you'd want it.    Professional installation highly recommended.        1999-2006       323Ci 325Ci 328Ci 330Ci

cleanDesc: RKP GT Carbon Fiber Roof Panel - 1x1 Weave - E46 Coupe
short-description: When the E46 M3 CSL was released, one of the central talking points of the vehicle was the cutting edge weight saving technologies that were utilized in its construction. The CSL was most notably distinguished from the standard E46 M3 by its various lightweight components. The largest of these is the carbon fiber-reinforced plastic (GFP) roof panel, which weighs over 13 pounds less than its conventional steel counterpart. Many enthusiasts sought after the BMW OEM roof to add to their vehicles, but the part was and is to this day only available to those with a CSL vin #. As an answer to the E46 M3 clients, RKP is proud to introduce the RKP E46 M3 carbon fiber roof panel. Their carbon roofs are constructed by hand at a local facility specializing in components for Grand Am, Time Attack, and various hill climb and formula car classes. Each roof has great fit and finish and saves a considerable amount of weight over the standard roof panel.

cleanDesc: RKP OEM Style Carbon Fiber & Kevlar Race Hood ‐ 2x2 Weave - E9...
short-description: While searching for places to shed weight on the E92 / E93 M3, most start with the obvious panels made of steel. When the factory gives you composite or aluminum panels already as a starting point the quest to shave the pounds of a performance car can become more difficult. The lightweight BWM M3 aluminum hood is a great part from the factory that no doubt saves tons of weight compared to its mainstream steel 3 series counterparts. Because aluminum is very soft, it requires a full backbone structure to support it so it doesn’t dent or deform easily. When using carbon fiber, RKP is able to rework the factory underside skeleton as well as use a foam hex cell core in the panel’s inner construction to produce a lightweight yet rigid structure. This formula yields a strong yet light hood with a 40% weight savings that’s as home on the street as it is on the road circuit. Features: – Full carbon composite construction by dry laid carbon and resin infusion. – Weighs only 13.6 lbs! ( OEM is 22.8 lbs. ) – Designed and Made in the USA

cleanDesc: Seibon M3 style carbon fiber hood - E90 3 series
short-description: Founded in 2003 Seibon Carbon excels in delivering premium quality carbon fiber products to those with discerning tastes. The process begins with the best carbon raw material manufactured in either USA or France; in fact it is the same stock that can be found on high performance racecars, battleships and satellites. Supporting race teams is one of Seibons' specialties and you will see their work in many different platforms and racing types. Drivers such as Michele Abbate in her Scion FRS racecar, Fredric Aasbo in his Formula D Scion tC and even team RS-R in Asian Formula D all rely solely on Seibon to get them to the podium. Using single piece construction, the carbon is laid inside of a mold instead of being wrapped around it. This allows for a much stronger piece in the end and allows much greater control when the resin is applied. Areas such as door hinges, hood latches and window regulator mounting points are reinforced so as to add strength and longevity through repeated use. Application of the resin is then accomplished using proprietary techniques that allow for a much more uniform coating than most competitors and yields a product that is lighter, since there is no excess. Finally the product is finished with a glossy clear coat this resists chipping and cracking and gives a glossy wet look. Inspection of the finished product is then performed to ensure there is no weave distortion in tight corners or complex bends. Features: Proprietary methods to lay wet carbon for a stronger and lighter product UV resistant resins, even a weathered part can be wet sanded and brought back to original finish Panels are 70% lighter than stock as opposed to competitors which come in around 50% lighter than stock. No black paint is used to hide imperfections along detail edges and creases. Partnered with SCCA and Formula Drift bringing their top quality fit and finish to the competition environment. This item fits the following BMWs: 2009-2012 E90 323i 323i 328i 328xi 335d 335i 335i xDrive 335xi

short-description: Founded in 2003 Seibon Carbon excels in delivering premium quality carbon fiber products to those with discerning tastes. The process begins with the best carbon raw material manufactured in either USA or France; in fact it is the same stock that can be found on high performance racecars, battleships and satellites. Supporting race teams is one of Seibons' specialties and you will see their work in many different platforms and racing types. Drivers such as Michele Abbate in her Scion FRS racecar, Fredric Aasbo in his Formula D Scion tC and even team RS-R in Asian Formula D all rely solely on Seibon to get them to the podium.

cleanDesc: RKP Carbon Fiber Trunk Spoiler - F90 M5
short-description: One of the most effective ways to weigh product design is to measure how it is perceived over a long period of time. There are countless aero products that have initial “shock and awe” value, but lose their panache as they age. With RKP, their design philosophy has been rooted in creating a lasting effect, a truly timeless design that can be enjoyed and admired for years to come. As physical testaments of their design success, RKP's E9X M3 and F10 M5 programs continue to be highly sought after—with their F8X M3 / M4 and F87 M2 components following suit. A tall bar they’ve set then for the almighty F90 M5. Not to fall victim to the dreaded sophomore slump, they knew this F10 successor would have to bring something special to the table. From the moment the entire F90 was 3D scanned, several meetings were held to help infuse the new M5’s unique design aesthetics into their suite of aerodynamic offerings. It’s almost befitting to have the trunk spoiler come at the tail end of their F90 program, a proverbial “cherry on top” of a comprehensive lineup. As a prominent design feature with RKP's M2 trunk spoiler, the roofline channel was carried into the new M5’s piece as well. This helps create some much-welcomed continuity to the rear of the car and gives a subtle nod to a similar treatment they integrated into their front lip design. As you’d expect from RKP, the F90 spoiler is sculpted to cover the full width of the trunk and offers a dynamic, upright curve to help promote extra downforce in addition to a stunning look. To help bring further attention to the piece, the RKP F90 M5 trunk spoiler is finished in hand lain 2x2 carbon twill and treated to a beautiful gloss. Product Details: 2x2 carbon fiber construction Perfect fitment Fits all F90 M5, G30 5-Series Instructions and adhesive promoter included Made in USA

cleanDesc: RKP GT Carbon Fiber Sport Trunk ‐ 1x1 Weave - E92 BMW
short-description: Designed, engineered, and manufactured in the USA, RKP's GT carbon sports trunk is the perfect addition to your E92 M3. Each trunk is constructed by hand from carbon fiber materials on the outside skin. Additional carbon fiber is added on the interior fiberglass structure in key areas for strength and rigidity, and finished with a black gel coat. From the factory, all 3 series models come with a heavy steel trunk. Mass amounts of weight savings from the rear most part of the car can be achieved by swapping to a lightweight version. Not only will you see a difference in handling, acceleration, and chassis response, but a stunning appearance as well. The intergraded spoiler on the trunks edge blends seamlessly with the factory body lines to create a true OEM look with perfect fitment. The trunks spoiler edge will offer additional aerodynamic down force to the rear of the car with minimal drag created. Specs: Factory trunk weight: 29.5 lbs RKP Carbon Sport Trunk: 11.0 lbs OVER 18lbs weight savings!

RKP Carbon Fiber Roof Panel - 2x2 Weave - F10 M5
short-description: One of our favorite additions to the M car was the use of a carbon fiber roof, first introduced on the E63 M6. BMW had of course already used advanced composites in the construction of their M cars for many years, but the use of a bare carbon fiber roof made a unique statement that set the M brand apart forever. Over the years RKP has helped E90 M3 and 1M car owners make the same statement by developing our own carbon fiber roof panels for the cars not given this privilege from the factory. RKP introduces the brand new carbon fiber roof panel for the F10 M5. This roof panel is available in a variety of weave styles to match OE carbon fiber or to deviate from the factory look instead. The RKP roof panel weighs in at a featherweight 11.5lbs, removing a tremendous amount of weight from the most critical area of the car. Features: – Full carbon composite construction by dry laid carbon and resin infusion. – OEM full replacement panel – Huge weight saving off the highest point on the car – Weighs only 11.5 lbs! – Designed and Made in the USA

We at Turner recommend APR Performance's long line of Carbon Fiber rear wings that are perfectly suited for the track, featuring light weight, heavy duty construction, and extremely high quality.

E9X M3 Genuine BMW Motorsport GT4 Front Splitter
short-description: Ultra-rare BMW Motorsport Racing part! This front splitter was optional equipment on the M3 GT4, a production-based race car built and sold by BMW Motorsport for the European GT4 race series. This front splitter is the REAL DEAL -- a true racing part that designed to add substantial downforce to the front end of the E9X chassis M3. As the M3 GT4 still used the same stock front bumper cover as your typical M3 street car, this splitter can be added to ANY 2008 or newer BMW M3.    Made of 100% carbon fiber, this front splitter includes fully functional brake duct openings for maximum cooling. As this is a true race part, made in very small numbers, the cost from BMW Motorsport reflects this -- but if you need a fully developed front splitter that was engineered by BMW Motorsport (and not just some "guess and test" styling piece) this is the splitter you want.      2008+    sedan  2008+    coupe  2008+    convertible
